<task id="011" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Dataverse Schema — Tool Registry Entity (sprk_toolregistry) with Extended LAVERN Metadata</title>
    <phase>Phase 1: Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>016, 020, 021, 022, 023, 024, 025, 026</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, solution, fields</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tool Registry is the LLM's discovery surface; field shape directly determines meta-tool behavior and Azure AI Search index schema (task 016); LAVERN-derived extended metadata is the critical differentiator from a vanilla tool registry; mis-shaped fields force rework across Phase 2</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches only `sprk_toolregistry` entity definition; disjoint from tasks 010 (action entities), 012 (sprk_gate_approval), 013 (sprk_aichatcontextmap)</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the `sprk_toolregistry` Dataverse entity carrying the full LAVERN-inspired extended metadata model (Classification, CostClass, LatencyClass, Idempotency, AuthMode, Discoverability, ModelTier, PhaseRestrictions, EvidenceRequired, IsAlwaysOnInAssistant, PromoteInContexts) per spec.md FR-07 and design §5. This entity feeds the Azure AI Search semantic index (task 016) and the meta-tools (`FindResources` / `GetResourceDetail` / `InvokeResource`).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE Dataverse schema engineer experienced with the `dataverse-create-schema` skill and with LAVERN's extended Tool Registry metadata pattern. You translate the spec's metadata field list into Dataverse Choice columns, JSON Memo fields, and boolean flags such that the BFF can deserialize directly to a strongly-typed `ToolMetadata` model without ambiguity.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_toolregistry` entity exists in dev with all 13 logical fields from spec.md FR-07 + design §5:

    1. **`resourceId`** — Text (primary name); globally unique Tool identifier
    2. **`displayName`** — Text
    3. **`description`** — Text(Memo)
    4. **`identityJson`** — Text(Memo); JSON: { ownerService, version, deprecated }
    5. **`inputSchema`** — Text(Memo); JSON Schema
    6. **`outputSchema`** — Text(Memo); JSON Schema
    7. **`classification`** — Choice: Deterministic / AI / Hybrid
    8. **`costClass`** — Choice: Free / Cheap / Expensive
    9. **`latencyClass`** — Choice: Sub100ms / Sub1s / Sub10s / LongRunning
    10. **`idempotency`** — Choice: Idempotent / NonIdempotent / IdempotentByKey
    11. **`authMode`** — Choice: Obo / AppOnly / None
    12. **`discoverabilityJson`** — Text(Memo); JSON: { keywords[], semanticDescription, sampleInvocations[] }
    13. **`modelTier`** — Choice: Premium / Standard / Fast / Embedding / NotApplicable
    14. **`phaseRestrictionsJson`** — Text(Memo); JSON array of phase deny-list entries
    15. **`evidenceRequired`** — Boolean
    16. **`isAlwaysOnInAssistant`** — Boolean
    17. **`promoteInContextsJson`** — Text(Memo); JSON string array of context tokens
    18. **`tenantId`** — Text; tenant scoping (NFR-05)

    Entity packed into the same solution as task 010's action entities. Deliverable: schema doc updated, smoke-tested by creating 3 sample Tool records (one Deterministic, one AI, one Hybrid).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      LAVERN Pattern: extended Tool Registry metadata is the key architectural differentiator that lets the LLM discover and reason about Tools via semantic search rather than hard-coded routing. The `Discoverability` JSON object specifically feeds the Azure AI Search `spaarke-resource-registry-index` (task 016) — `semanticDescription` becomes the semantic-search field.

      The 11-axis metadata schema (Classification through PromoteInContexts) maps to design §5 LAVERN-derived fields and spec.md FR-07. Do NOT add fields beyond this set without a spec change. Do NOT collapse choice columns into free text — the metadata is contract-binding for the LLM.

      `PhaseRestrictions` is the data backing for the mechanical Phase deny-tools enforcement at `IToolHandlerRegistry` dispatch (spec FR-22, design §5). It is a JSON array because phase deny-lists are arbitrary length and variable.

      `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant` is the boolean toggle that surfaces a Tool on every Assistant session alongside the meta-tools. The 3 always-on foundational Tools (`SearchDocuments`, `QueryDataverse`, `GetCurrentEntityContext`) will all carry `isAlwaysOnInAssistant = true`.

      `EvidenceRequired` is a runtime guard (NFR-06 guardrail #3) — Tools with this flag refuse to execute without source citations in their inputs. The field is just storage here; the runtime guard lives at the dispatch layer.

      Tenant scoping: `tenantId` text field, required. Tool Registry semantic index uses tenant-filtered queries (NFR-05).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md</file>
