  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, task 001 status is ✅. Load the `dataverse-create-schema` skill. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Read spec.md FR-07, design §5 (Tool Registry section), and lavern-pattern-assessment.md (Pattern: extended Tool Registry metadata). Confirm the 13-field set is fully understood before scripting.</step>
    <step order="2">Identify target solution from task 010's decision (`notes/decisions/solution-targeting.md`). Use the same solution for atomic deploy.</step>
    <step order="3">Author the entity schema as Python / Web API script. Order: create the 6 global Choice option-sets first (Classification, CostClass, LatencyClass, Idempotency, AuthMode, ModelTier), then create the entity, then add the 13 columns referencing those option-sets.</step>
    <step order="4">Run the schema script against the dev environment. Confirm via Web API GET on the EntityDefinition that all 13 columns landed with correct types and Choice value labels.</step>
    <step order="5">Pack the entity into the same solution as task 010 entities. Verify the export contains `sprk_toolregistry` + the 6 global option-sets.</step>
    <step order="6">Smoke-test in maker portal: create 3 sample records — one Deterministic Tool (`SendEmail`, CostClass=Free, LatencyClass=Sub1s, Idempotency=NonIdempotent, AuthMode=Obo), one AI Tool (`SummarizeMatter`, Classification=AI, ModelTier=Standard, CostClass=Cheap), one Hybrid (`FindSimilarMatters`, Classification=Hybrid). Verify all Choice labels render correctly, JSON fields accept valid JSON, booleans toggle.</step>
    <step order="7">Append the entity definition to `docs/data-model/action-engine-entities.md` (created by task 010). Include the field-by-field list with type + allowed values for each Choice.</step>
    <step order="8">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the schema script + the schema doc update; `adr-check` confirms ADR-002 (no plugins) and ADR-019 (custom-API note for later phases).</step>
